{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889617939,"sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b45023c001WqLv751YlFFAZm","messageID":"msg_d7b44e5e0001RahWOzsc4TQZNd","sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4af136e3ed4a4d38b3de6dd63a7594a0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775889617907,"end":1775889617937}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889617941,"sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b4505d9001k0qEt2E9Ryqrx6","messageID":"msg_d7b44e5e0001RahWOzsc4TQZNd","sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-198667122de9436c8dc2d31a2e2841aa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775889617911,"end":1775889617940}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889617947,"sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b450b18001CubEnMclts29oL","messageID":"msg_d7b44e5e0001RahWOzsc4TQZNd","sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b89bbb30466e42118344adcacf0dc53a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) |\n8: | Module | `.github` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: [TO BE FILLED: Define scope for CI/CD GitHub Actions]\n16: \n17: ## Out of Scope\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Define out of scope items]\n20: \n21: ## Dependencies\n22: \n23: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n24: |------------|---------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ## Deliverables\n28: \n29: | File | Description |\n30: |------|-------------|\n31: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: \n35: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n36: \n37: ## References\n38: \n39: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n\n(End of file - total 39 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) |\n| Module | `.github` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define scope for CI/CD GitHub Actions]\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define out of scope items]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/spec.md","time":{"start":1775889617913,"end":1775889617946}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889617950,"sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","part":{"id":"prt_d7b450fb60013qCEqQBlu3ogyD","messageID":"msg_d7b44e5e0001RahWOzsc4TQZNd","sessionID":"ses_284bb4d27ffe0nWq2xA25JMCqO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5b616a4201b744579dcb16eb25fefc55","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) |\n8: | Module | `.github` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 (completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### High-Level CI/CD Pipeline Flow\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                         GitHub Actions CI/CD Pipeline                            │\n22: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n23: │                                                                                  │\n24: │  ┌──────────────┐                                                                │\n25: │  │ Pull Request │                                                                │\n26: │  │  to main     │                                                                │\n27: │  └──────────────┘                                                                │\n28: │         │                                                                        │\n29: │         ▼                                                                        │\n30: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n31: │  │                    Triggered Workflows (Parallel)                           ││\n32: │  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤│\n33: │  │                                                                              ││\n34: │  │  ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌────────────────────┐ ││\n35: │  │  │   main.yml   │ │   e2e.yml    │ │   lint.yml   │ │ test-coverage.yml  │ ││\n36: │  │  │ Docker Build │ │ E2E on Kind  │ │ Go golangci  │ │ Go test + coverage │ ││\n37: │  │  └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └────────────────────┘ ││\n38: │  │                                                                              ││\n39: │  │  ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌────────────────────┐ ││\n40: │  │  │ python-sdk-  │ │ python-lint  │ │ codegen-     │ │ copyright-check.yml│ ││\n41: │  │  │ tests.yml    │ │ .yml (Ruff)  │ │ check.yml    │ │ Copyright headers  │ ││\n42: │  │  └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └────────────────────┘ ││\n43: │  │                                                                              ││\n44: │  │  ┌──────────────────┐                                                        ││\n45: │  │  │   codespell.yml   │                                                        ││\n46: │  │  │ Spelling check    │                                                        ││\n47: │  │  └──────────────────┘                                                        ││\n48: │  │                                                                              ││\n49: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n50: │                                                                                  │\n51: │  ┌──────────────┐                                                                │\n52: │  │ Push to main │                                                                │\n53: │  │ or v* tag    │                                                                │\n54: │  └──────────────┘                                                                │\n55: │         │                                                                        │\n56: │         ▼                                                                        │\n57: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n58: │  │                                                                              ││\n59: │  │  ┌───────────────────────┐                                                  ││\n60: │  │  │ build-push-release.yml │                                                  ││\n61: │  │  │ Build + Push to ghcr.io│                                                  ││\n62: │  │  │ (workloadmanager,      │                                                  ││\n63: │  │  │  router, picod)        │                                                  ││\n64: │  │  └───────────────────────┘                                                  ││\n65: │  │                                                                              ││\n66: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n67: │                                                                                  │\n68: │  ┌───────────────────┐                                                           │\n69: │  │ Push tag          │                                                           │\n70: │  │ dify-plugin/v*    │                                                           │\n71: │  └───────────────────┘                                                           │\n72: │         │                                                                        │\n73: │         ▼                                                                        │\n74: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n75: │  │                                                                              ││\n76: │  │  ┌───────────────────────────┐                                              ││\n77: │  │  │ dify-plugin-publish.yml    │                                              ││\n78: │  │  │ Package + PR to            │                                              ││\n79: │  │  │ langgenius/dify-plugins    │                                              ││\n80: │  │  └───────────────────────────┘                                              ││\n81: │  │                                                                              ││\n82: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n83: │                                                                                  │\n84: │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐                                               │\n85: │  │ pull_request_target           │                                               │\n86: │  │ (labeled, synchronize)        │                                               │\n87: │  └───────────────────────────────┘                                               │\n88: │         │                                                                        │\n89: │         ▼                                                                        │\n90: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n91: │  │                                                                              ││\n92: │  │  ┌───────────────────────────────┐                                          ││\n93: │  │  │ workflows-approve.yml          │                                          ││\n94: │  │  │ Auto-approve for trusted       │                                          ││\n95: │  │  │ contributors or ok-to-test     │                                          ││\n96: │  │  └───────────────────────────────┘                                          ││\n97: │  │                                                                              ││\n98: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n99: │                                                                                  │\n100: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Workflow Dependency Graph\n104: \n105: ```\n106:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n107:                     │    Repository       │\n108:                     │  (agentcube repo)   │\n109:                     └─────────────────────┘\n110:                               │\n111:            ┌──────────────────┼──────────────────┐\n112:            │                  │                  │\n113:            ▼                  ▼                  ▼\n114: ┌──────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐\n115: │   Makefile       │ │   test/e2e/      │ │   sdk-python/    │\n116: │   Targets:       │ │   run_e2e.sh     │ │   pytest tests   │\n117: │   - docker-build │ │   fixtures       │ │                  │\n118: │   - lint         │ │                  │ │                  │\n119: │   - gen-check    │ │                  │ │                  │\n120: │   - e2e          │ │                  │ │                  │\n121: └──────────────────┘ └──────────────────┘ └──────────────────┘\n122:            │                  │                  │\n123:            │                  │                  │\n124:            ▼                  ▼                  ▼\n125: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n126: │                    GitHub Actions                            │\n127: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│\n128: │  │ Workflows consume external resources:                   ││\n129: │  │ - actions/checkout@v4                                   ││\n130: │  │ - actions/setup-go@v5                                   ││\n131: │  │ - actions/setup-python@v5                               ││\n132: │  │ - docker/setup-buildx-action@v3                         ││\n133: │  │ - docker/login-action@v3                                ││\n134: │  │ - helm/kind-action@v1                                   ││\n135: │  │ - dorny/paths-filter@v3                                 ││\n136: │  │ - codecov/codecov-action@v4                             ││\n137: │  │ - actions/github-script@v7                              ││\n138: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│\n139: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Component Relationships\n143: \n144: ```\n145: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n146: │                      Workflow-to-Makefile Mapping                            │\n147: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n148: │                                                                              │\n149: │  Workflow                  Makefile Target        Build Output               │\n150: │  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────  │\n151: │                                                                              │\n152: │  main.yml                  docker-build          workloadmanager:latest      │\n153: │                                                                              │\n154: │  e2e.yml                   docker-build          workloadmanager:latest      │\n155: │                            docker-build-router   agentcube-router:latest     │\n156: │                            docker-build-picod    picod:latest                │\n157: │                            e2e                   —                           │\n158: │                            e2e-clean             —                           │\n159: │                                                                              │\n160: │  lint.yml                  lint                  —                           │\n161: │                                                                              │\n162: │  test-coverage.yml         go test               coverage.out                │\n163: │                                                                              │\n164: │  codegen-check.yml         gen-check             —                           │\n165: │                                                                              │\n166: │  copyright-check.yml       gen-copyright         —                           │\n167: │                                                                              │\n168: │  build-push-release.yml    docker-buildx-push    workloadmanager:${TAG}      │\n169: │                            docker-buildx-push-   agentcube-router:${TAG}      │\n170: │                              router                                             │\n171: │                            docker-buildx-push-   picod:${TAG}                 │\n172: │                              picod                                              │\n173: │                                                                              │\n174: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## Data Structures\n180: \n181: ### Workflow YAML Structure\n182: \n183: Each workflow follows this canonical structure:\n184: \n185: ```yaml\n186: name: \"<Descriptive Workflow Name>\"\n187: on:\n188:   <trigger-specification>\n189: \n190: jobs:\n191:   <job-name>:\n192:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n193:     if: <conditional-expression>\n194:     steps:\n195:       - name: \"<Step Description>\"\n196:         uses: <action-reference>\n197:         with:\n198:           <action-inputs>\n199:         env:\n200:           <environment-variables>\n201: ```\n202: \n203: ### Path Filter Definitions\n204: \n205: ```yaml\n206: filters:\n207:   lint:\n208:     - '**/*.go'\n209:     - 'go.mod'\n210:     - 'go.sum'\n211:     - '.golangci.yml'\n212:     - '.github/workflows/lint.yml'\n213:   \n214:   sdk:\n215:     - 'sdk-python/**'\n216:   \n217:   python:\n218:     - 'cmd/cli/**'\n219:     - 'sdk-python/**'\n220:     - 'example/**'\n221:     - 'test/**/*.py'\n222:     - 'pyproject.toml'\n223:     - '.github/workflows/python-lint.yml'\n224:   \n225:   coverage:\n226:     - '**'\n227:     - '!*.md'\n228:     - '!*.svg'\n229:     - '!*.png'\n230:   \n231:   codegen:\n232:     - 'pkg/apis/**'\n233:     - 'hack/**'\n234:     - '.github/workflows/**'\n235:     - 'Makefile'\n236:   \n237:   copyright:\n238:     - '**'\n239:     - '!*.md'\n240:     - '!*.svg'\n241:     - '!*.png'\n242:     - '!docs/**'\n243:     - '!.github/**'\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Workflow Output Variables\n247: \n248: ```yaml\n249: outputs:\n250:   lint-changed: ${{ steps.filter.outputs.lint }}\n251:   sdk-changed: ${{ steps.filter.outputs.sdk }}\n252:   python-changed: ${{ steps.filter.outputs.python }}\n253:   coverage-changed: ${{ steps.filter.outputs.coverage }}\n254:   codegen-changed: ${{ steps.filter.outputs.codegen }}\n255:   copyright-changed: ${{ steps.filter.outputs.copyright }}\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### Artifact Specifications\n259: \n260: ```yaml\n261: artifacts:\n262:   go-coverage:\n263:     path: coverage.out\n264:     retention-days: 7\n265:     \n266:   e2e-logs:\n267:     path: e2e-logs/\n268:     retention-days: 7\n269:     if-no-files-found: warn\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### Environment Variable Contract\n273: \n274: ```yaml\n275: env:\n276:   ARTIFACTS_PATH: ${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs\n277:   TAG: ${{ github.ref_type == 'tag' && github.ref_name || 'latest' }}\n278:   IMAGE_REGISTRY: ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}\n279:   WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE: workloadmanager:${{ env.TAG }}\n280:   ROUTER_IMAGE: agentcube-router:${{ env.TAG }}\n281:   PICOD_IMAGE: picod:${{ env.TAG }}\n282:   AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE: agentcube\n283:   WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: http://localhost:${{ env.WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT }}\n284:   ROUTER_URL: http://localhost:${{ env.ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT }}\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ## API Contracts\n290: \n291: ### Workflow Trigger Specification\n292: \n293: ```yaml\n294: on:\n295:   pull_request:\n296:     branches:\n297:       - main\n298:       - 'release-*'\n299:     types:\n300:       - opened\n301:       - synchronize\n302:       - reopened\n303:   \n304:   push:\n305:     branches:\n306:       - main\n307:     tags:\n308:       - 'v*.*.*'\n309:       - 'v*.*.*-*'\n310:       - 'dify-plugin/v*'\n311:   \n312:   merge_group:\n313:   \n314:   workflow_call:\n315:     inputs:\n316:       CODECOV_TOKEN:\n317:         description: 'Codecov upload token'\n318:         required: false\n319:         type: string\n320:     secrets:\n321:       CODECOV_TOKEN:\n322:         description: 'Codecov token for coverage upload'\n323:         required: false\n324:   \n325:   pull_request_target:\n326:     branches:\n327:       - main\n328:       - 'release-**'\n329:     types:\n330:       - labeled\n331:       - synchronize\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ### GitHub Actions API Contract\n335: \n336: ```yaml\n337: actions_api:\n338:   checkout:\n339:     uses: actions/checkout@v4\n340:     with:\n341:       fetch-depth: 0\n342:   \n343:   setup_go:\n344:     uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n345:     with:\n346:       go-version: '1.24'\n347:       cache: true\n348:   \n349:   setup_go_123:\n350:     uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n351:     with:\n352:       go-version: '1.23'\n353:       cache: true\n354:   \n355:   setup_go_1244:\n356:     uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n357:     with:\n358:       go-version: '1.24.4'\n359:       cache: true\n360:   \n361:   setup_python:\n362:     uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n363:     with:\n364:       python-version: '3.12'\n365:       cache: pip\n366:   \n367:   setup_python_310:\n368:     uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n369:     with:\n370:       python-version: '3.10'\n371:       cache: pip\n372:   \n373:   setup_buildx:\n374:     uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3\n375:   \n376:   docker_login:\n377:     uses: docker/login-action@v3\n378:     with:\n379:       registry: ghcr.io\n380:       username: ${{ github.actor }}\n381:       password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n382:   \n383:   paths_filter:\n384:     uses: dorny/paths-filter@v3\n385:     with:\n386:       filters: .github/workflows/filters.yaml\n387:   \n388:   kind_action:\n389:     uses: helm/kind-action@v1\n390:     with:\n391:       install_only: true\n392:       version: v0.30.0\n393:   \n394:   codecov:\n395:     uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n396:     with:\n397:       file: coverage.out\n398:       fail_ci_if_error: false\n399:       token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}\n400:   \n401:   github_script:\n402:     uses: actions/github-script@v7\n403:     with:\n404:       script: |\n405:         <inline-script>\n406: ```\n407: \n408: ### Makefile Target Contract\n409: \n410: ```yaml\n411: makefile_targets:\n412:   docker-build:\n413:     description: Build workload manager Docker image\n414:     prerequisites: Docker, Buildx\n415:     output: workloadmanager:latest\n416:     \n417:   docker-build-router:\n418:     description: Build router Docker image\n419:     prerequisites: Docker, Buildx\n420:     output: agentcube-router:latest\n421:     \n422:   docker-build-picod:\n423:     description: Build picod Docker image\n424:     prerequisites: Docker, Buildx\n425:     output: picod:latest\n426:     \n427:   docker-buildx-push:\n428:     description: Push workload manager to registry\n429:     env_vars:\n430:       - IMAGE_REGISTRY\n431:       - WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE\n432:     prerequisites: docker/login-action\n433:     \n434:   docker-buildx-push-router:\n435:     description: Push router to registry\n436:     env_vars:\n437:       - IMAGE_REGISTRY\n438:       - ROUTER_IMAGE\n439:     prerequisites: docker/login-action\n440:     \n441:   docker-buildx-push-picod:\n442:     description: Push picod to registry\n443:     env_vars:\n444:       - IMAGE_REGISTRY\n445:       - PICOD_IMAGE\n446:     prerequisites: docker/login-action\n447:     \n448:   lint:\n449:     description: Run golangci-lint\n450:     prerequisites: Go 1.24, .golangci.yml\n451:     \n452:   gen-check:\n453:     description: Verify generated code matches committed version\n454:     command_sequence:\n455:       - make gen-all\n456:       - git diff --exit-code\n457:     prerequisites: Go 1.24.4\n458:     \n459:   gen-copyright:\n460:     description: Generate copyright headers\n461:     prerequisites: moreutils (sponge)\n462:     \n463:   e2e:\n464:     description: Run E2E tests\n465:     prerequisites: Kind v0.30.0, Go 1.23, agent-sandbox CRDs\n466:     \n467:   e2e-clean:\n468:     description: Cleanup E2E resources\n469:     command: kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ### Kind Cluster Configuration\n473: \n474: ```yaml\n475: kind_cluster:\n476:   name: agentcube-e2e\n477:   version: v0.30.0\n478:   \n479:   images_loaded:\n480:     - registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:v0.1.1\n481:     - python:3.9-slim\n482:     - workloadmanager:latest\n483:     - agentcube-router:latest\n484:     - picod:latest\n485:     - redis:7-alpine\n486:   \n487:   crds_applied:\n488:     - https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/v0.1.1/manifest.yaml\n489:     - https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/v0.1.1/extensions.yaml\n490:   \n491:   helm_chart:\n492:     path: manifests/charts/base\n493:     release: agentcube\n494:     namespace: agentcube\n495:     values:\n496:       redis.address: redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\n497:       redis.password: \"\"\n498:       workloadmanager.image.repository: workloadmanager\n499:       workloadmanager.image.tag: latest\n500:       router.image.repository: agentcube-router\n501:       router.image.tag: latest\n502:       router.rbac.create: true\n503:       router.serviceAccountName: agentcube-router\n504: ```\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Error Handling\n509: \n510: ### Workflow Failure Categories\n511: \n512: | Category | Description | Recovery Action |\n513: |----------|-------------|-----------------|\n514: | `BuildFailure` | Docker build or compilation error | Log output, fail job |\n515: | `LintFailure` | golangci-lint or Ruff violations | Report violations, fail job |\n516: | `TestFailure` | Unit test or E2E test failure | Upload artifacts, fail job |\n517: | `CodegenDrift` | Generated code differs from committed | Show diff, fail job |\n518: | `CopyrightDrift` | Copyright headers mismatch | Show diff, fail job |\n519: | `SpellingError` | codespell detected typos | Report errors, fail job |\n520: | `RegistryAuthFailure` | Docker login failed | Log error, fail job |\n521: | `KindSetupFailure` | Kind cluster creation failed | Upload logs, fail job |\n522: | `CoverageUploadFailure` | Codecov upload failed | Continue (non-blocking) |\n523: \n524: ### Conditional Failure Handling\n525: \n526: ```yaml\n527: failure_handling:\n528:   e2e_failure:\n529:     if: failure()\n530:     steps:\n531:       - name: Upload E2E logs\n532:         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n533:         with:\n534:           name: e2e-logs\n535:           path: e2e-logs/\n536:   \n537:   e2e_cleanup:\n538:     if: always()\n539:     steps:\n540:       - name: Cleanup E2E\n541:         run: make e2e-clean\n542:         continue-on-error: true\n543:   \n544:   coverage_upload:\n545:     if: success()\n546:     steps:\n547:       - name: Upload to Codecov\n548:         uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4\n549:         with:\n550:           fail_ci_if_error: false\n551: ```\n552: \n553: ### Path Filter Skip Logic\n554: \n555: ```yaml\n556: path_filter_skip:\n557:   pattern: |\n558:     if: steps.filter.outputs.<filter-name> != 'true'\n559:     run: echo \"No <filter-name> changes detected, skipping job\"\n560:     \n561:   skip_job: |\n562:     jobs:\n563:       <job-name>:\n564:         if: ${{ needs.<previous-job>.outputs.<filter-name> == 'true' }}\n565: ```\n566: \n567: ### Secrets Handling\n568: \n569: ```yaml\n570: secrets_contract:\n571:   GITHUB_TOKEN:\n572:     scope: write (for gh pr create)\n573:     usage: Registry login, GitHub API\n574:     built_in: true\n575:   \n576:   CODECOV_TOKEN:\n577:     scope: read\n578:     usage: Codecov upload authentication\n579:     optional: true\n580:     declared_in: workflow_call\n581:     \n582:   PLUGIN_ACTION:\n583:     scope: write (for cross-repo checkout and PR)\n584:     usage: Dify plugin publish workflow\n585:     required_for: dify-plugin-publish.yml\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ### Timeout Configuration\n589: \n590: ```yaml\n591: timeout_config:\n592:   job_timeout:\n593:     default: 30m\n594:     e2e: 45m\n595:     \n596:   step_timeout:\n597:     go_test: 10m\n598:     e2e_run: 30m\n599:     docker_build: 15m\n600:     docker_push: 20m\n601: ```\n602: \n603: ---\n604: \n605: ## Testing Strategy\n606: \n607: ### Workflow Validation Matrix\n608: \n609: | Workflow | Validation Method | Test Command |\n610: |----------|-------------------|--------------|\n611: | `main.yml` | Docker build success | `make docker-build` |\n612: | `e2e.yml` | E2E test execution | `make e2e` in Kind cluster |\n613: | `lint.yml` | golangci-lint pass | `make lint` |\n614: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | pytest pass | `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n615: | `python-lint.yml` | Ruff pass | `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` |\n616: | `test-coverage.yml` | Coverage generation | `go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/...` |\n617: | `codegen-check.yml` | No drift | `make gen-check && git diff --exit-code` |\n618: | `copyright-check.yml` | No drift | `make gen-copyright && git diff --exit-code` |\n619: | `codespell.yml` | No spelling errors | `codespell --check-filenames .` |\n620: | `build-push-release.yml` | Registry push | `make docker-buildx-push` (with registry auth) |\n621: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Plugin package | `dify-plugin package` |\n622: | `workflows-approve.yml` | API approval | GitHub API `approveWorkflowRun` |\n623: \n624: ### E2E Test Sequence\n625: \n626: ```yaml\n627: e2e_test_sequence:\n628:   setup:\n629:     - name: Create Kind cluster\n630:       command: kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n631:     \n632:     - name: Load images\n633:       command: kind load docker-image <image-list>\n634:     \n635:     - name: Apply CRDs\n636:       command: kubectl apply --validate=false -f <crd-urls>\n637:     \n638:     - name: Install Helm chart\n639:       command: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base\n640:     \n641:     - name: Port-forward services\n642:       command: kubectl port-forward svc/<service>\n643:     \n644:     - name: Health check\n645:       command: curl http://localhost:<port>/health\n646:     \n647:   test_execution:\n648:     - name: Go E2E tests\n649:       env:\n650:         WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: http://localhost:8080\n651:         ROUTER_URL: http://localhost:8081\n652:         API_TOKEN: <generated-token>\n653:       command: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n654:     \n655:     - name: Python E2E tests\n656:       command: python test_codeinterpreter.py\n657:     \n658:   cleanup:\n659:     - name: Delete Kind cluster\n660:       command: kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n661:       if: always()\n662:     \n663:     - name: Remove temp files\n664:       command: rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox\n665:       if: always()\n666: ```\n667: \n668: ### Coverage Test Specification\n669: \n670: ```yaml\n671: coverage_test_spec:\n672:   command: |\n673:     go test -race -v \\\n674:       -coverprofile=coverage.out \\\n675:       -coverpkg=./pkg/... \\\n676:       ./pkg/...\n677:   \n678:   package_scope: ./pkg/...\n679:   \n680:   race_detector: enabled\n681:   \n682:   output:\n683:     coverage.out: coverage profile\n684:     step_summary: coverage percentage\n685:   \n686:   upload:\n687:     provider: Codecov\n688:     file: coverage.out\n689:     fail_on_error: false\n690: ```\n691: \n692: ### Python Test Specification\n693: \n694: ```yaml\n695: python_test_spec:\n696:   sdk_tests:\n697:     working_directory: sdk-python\n698:     python_version: '3.12'\n699:     setup:\n700:       - pip install pytest\n701:       - pip install -e .\n702:     command: python -m pytest tests/ -v\n703:   \n704:   e2e_python:\n705:     working_directory: test/e2e\n706:     python_version: '3.12'\n707:     venv: /tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv\n708:     setup:\n709:       - python3 -m venv $E2E_VENV_DIR\n710:       - pip install -e ./sdk-python\n711:     command: python test_codeinterpreter.py\n712: ```\n713: \n714: ### Workflow Self-Test Commands\n715: \n716: ```yaml\n717: workflow_self_test:\n718:   validate_yaml:\n719:     command: yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml\n720:     \n721:   check_syntax:\n722:     command: gh workflow view <workflow-name>\n723:     \n724:   test_trigger:\n725:     command: gh workflow run <workflow-name> --ref <branch>\n726:     \n727:   verify_artifacts:\n728:     command: gh run download <run-id>\n729: ```\n730: \n731: ---\n732: \n733: ## File Structure\n734: \n735: ```\n736: .github/\n737: ├── workflows/\n738: │   ├── main.yml                    # PR Docker build verification\n739: │   ├── e2e.yml                     # E2E tests on Kind\n740: │   ├── lint.yml                    # Go lint with path filter\n741: │   ├── python-sdk-tests.yml        # Python SDK pytest\n742: │   ├── python-lint.yml             # Python Ruff lint\n743: │   ├── test-coverage.yml           # Go coverage + Codecov\n744: │   ├── codegen-check.yml           # Generated code drift\n745: │   ├── copyright-check.yml         # Copyright header check\n746: │   ├── codespell.yml               # Spelling verification\n747: │   ├── build-push-release.yml      # Multi-arch image push\n748: │   ├── dify-plugin-publish.yml     # Dify plugin release\n749: │   └── workflows-approve.yml       # Auto-approve trusted\n750: └── filters.yaml                    # (optional) Centralized path filters\n751: ```\n752: \n753: ### Workflow File Size Estimates\n754: \n755: | Workflow | Estimated Lines | Complexity |\n756: |----------|-----------------|------------|\n757: | `main.yml` | ~30 | Low |\n758: | `e2e.yml` | ~80 | High |\n759: | `lint.yml` | ~50 | Medium |\n760: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | ~40 | Low |\n761: | `python-lint.yml` | ~50 | Medium |\n762: | `test-coverage.yml` | ~60 | Medium |\n763: | `codegen-check.yml` | ~50 | Medium |\n764: | `copyright-check.yml` | ~50 | Medium |\n765: | `codespell.yml` | ~80 | Medium |\n766: | `build-push-release.yml` | ~100 | High |\n767: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | ~120 | High |\n768: | `workflows-approve.yml` | ~70 | High |\n769: \n770: ---\n771: \n772: ## Dependencies\n773: \n774: ### GitHub Actions Dependencies\n775: \n776: | Action | Version | Purpose |\n777: |--------|---------|---------|\n778: | `actions/checkout` | v4 | Repository checkout with history |\n779: | `actions/setup-go` | v5 | Go toolchain (versions 1.23, 1.24, 1.24.4) |\n780: | `actions/setup-python` | v5 | Python toolchain (versions 3.10, 3.12) |\n781: | `docker/setup-buildx-action` | v3 | Docker Buildx setup |\n782: | `docker/login-action` | v3 | Container registry authentication |\n783: | `helm/kind-action` | v1 | Kind cluster tooling (v0.30.0) |\n784: | `dorny/paths-filter` | v3 | Path-based job filtering |\n785: | `codecov/codecov-action` | v4 | Coverage report upload |\n786: | `actions/upload-artifact` | v4 | Artifact storage |\n787: | `actions/github-script` | v7 | GitHub API scripting |\n788: \n789: ### Tool Dependencies\n790: \n791: | Tool | Version | Purpose |\n792: |------|---------|---------|\n793: | Go | 1.23, 1.24, 1.24.4 | Go builds and tests |\n794: | Python | 3.10, 3.12 | Python lint and SDK tests |\n795: | Docker | latest | Container builds |\n796: | Buildx | latest | Multi-architecture builds |\n797: | Kind | v0.30.0 | Kubernetes in Docker |\n798: | golangci-lint | (project default) | Go linting |\n799: | Ruff | latest | Python linting |\n800: | pytest | latest | Python testing |\n801: | codespell | latest | Spelling check |\n802: | yq | latest | YAML processing (dify-plugin) |\n803: | dify-plugin CLI | 0.0.6 | Plugin packaging |\n804: \n805: ### External Resources\n806: \n807: | Resource | URL | Purpose |\n808: |----------|-----|---------|\n809: | agent-sandbox CRDs | github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases | Kind cluster setup |\n810: | agent-sandbox controller | registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox | E2E dependencies |\n811: | python:3.9-slim | Docker Hub | Echo agent workload |\n812: | redis:7-alpine | Docker Hub | Session store |\n813: | ghcr.io | GitHub Container Registry | Image publication |\n814: | Codecov | codecov.com | Coverage reporting |\n815: | dify-plugins repo | github.com/langgenius/dify-plugins | Plugin publication |\n816: \n817: ---\n818: \n819: ## Implementation Notes\n820: \n821: ### Workflow Naming Convention\n822: \n823: - Filenames: lowercase with hyphens (e.g., `main.yml`, `e2e.yml`)\n824: - Workflow `name`: descriptive titles (e.g., \"Agentcube CI Workflow\")\n825: - Job names: descriptive with underscores (e.g., `build`, `e2e-test`, `coverage`)\n826: - Step names: action-oriented descriptions\n827: \n828: ### Path Filter Pattern\n829: \n830: - Use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for all path-sensitive workflows\n831: - Filters defined inline or in separate `filters.yaml` file\n832: - Output used in `if:` conditions for job skipping\n833: - Inverted patterns (`!*.md`) for exclusion\n834: \n835: ### Kind Cluster Isolation\n836: \n837: - Use `install_only: true` to prevent `helm/kind-action` from creating cluster\n838: - Cluster name: `agentcube-e2e`\n839: - Cleanup in `always()` block to ensure resource release\n840: - Logs collected in `ARTIFACTS_PATH` on failure\n841: \n842: ### Registry Authentication\n843: \n844: - Use `GITHUB_TOKEN` (built-in) for `ghcr.io` authentication\n845: - No long-lived secrets required for main workflow\n846: - `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for cross-repo operations in dify-plugin workflow\n847: \n848: ### Coverage Upload Strategy\n849: \n850: - Upload `coverage.out` as artifact first\n851: - Codecov upload is non-blocking (`fail_ci_if_error: false`)\n852: - `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional via `workflow_call` secrets\n853: \n854: ### First-time Contributor Handling\n855: \n856: - Use `pull_request_target` for access to repo secrets\n857: - Check contributor PR count via GitHub API\n858: - Approve `action_required` workflow runs for trusted contributors\n859: - `ok-to-test` label overrides first-time check\n860: \n861: ---\n862: \n863: ## References\n864: \n865: - Spec: `changes/AR-034/spec.md`\n866: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md`\n867: - Proposal: `changes/AR-034/proposal.md`\n868: - Tasks: `changes/AR-034/tasks.md`\n869: - CI/CD Reference: `ci-cd/design.md`\n870: - CI/CD Specification: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n871: - E2E Test Script: `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n872: - Makefile: `Makefile`\n873: - GitHub Actions Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n874: - Kind Docs: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n875: - Docker Buildx: https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/\n\n(End of file - total 875 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) |\n| Module | `.github` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 (completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level CI/CD Pipeline Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/design.md","time":{"start":1775889617915,"end":1775889617948}}}}
